Package: QMRA
Type: Package
Title: Parametric Models for Quantitative Microbial Risk Assessment
Version: 0.0.6
Date: 2014-03-07
Authors@R: c(person("Brecht", "Devleesschauwer",
             role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "Brecht.Devleesschauwer@UGent.be"),
             person("Niko", "Speybroeck", role = "aut"),
             person("Christel", "Faes", role = "aut"))
Author: Brecht Devleesschauwer [aut, cre],
        Niko Speybroeck [aut],
        Christel Faes [aut]
Maintainer: Brecht Devleesschauwer <Brecht.Devleesschauwer@UGent.be>
BugReports: https://github.com/brechtdv/QMRA/issues
Description: The QMRA package provideds Maximum-likelihood and Bayesian parametric methods for exposure assessment and dose-response assessment. IMPORTANT: the Bayesian methods in the QMRA package call on JAGS (Just Another Gibbs Sampler), which therefore has to be available on the user's system. JAGS can be downloaded from http://mcmc-jags.sourceforge.net/
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0), rjags, coda, methods, lme4, stats4, SuppDists, HyperbolicDist
SystemRequirements: jags (>= 3.2.0)
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: yes